# Research Notes

## Problem Observations
- Searching for textbooks for the lowest price can be time-consuming.
- Prices can vary a lot across different platforms.
- There is no single system that combines all useful features in one place.

## Thought Process
- Features were based on student experience.
- Focused on saving time and money.
- Designed around what students would realistically use.

## Existing Tools and Limitations
- Existing comparison tools require users to switch between multiple sites.
- Many tools lack strong filtering options.
- ISBN and edition verification is not always reliable.
- Users still need to manually verify listings.

## Key Insights
- Students want both low price and correct textbook edition.
- Students want convenience and efficiency in one place.
- Students want to avoid misleading or irrelevant listings.

## Derived Needs
- Ability to search by title or ISBN.
- Verification of correct edition before showing results.
- Aggregation of listings into a single output.
- Filtering options for price, condition, format, and vendor.
- Clear and ranked results for easy comparison.
